body:
‘Good Omens’: TV Review

And so the two end up becoming, at first, complicit in a scheme to cover for the other and make their long lives easier. And then they become friends. And then they become the best of all friends.

And it’s no stretch at all to imagine, after you’ve seen all six episodes of Good Omens, that this might be one of the most convincing, lovingly told (if chaste) gay love stories in TV history.

description:
This is really a “mind the tags” fic, but I’m actually fairly happy with how it turned out. It demanded to be written, and then it wouldn’t stop growing, but with only minor suffering on my part, I managed to finish it before the release of the tv show like I wanted. 

In an alternate universe, Hell gives Crowley a reward for the Spanish Inquisition. That reward is an angel they’ve been holding captive. The results are unexpected.
